Project Methodology:

CRISP-DM
1) Business Understanding
	• Problem statement: Fraud transaction prediction
	• Process Flow definition
	• Domain concepts 
		○ Behavioral - Transactional, Web activities
		○ Customer Demographic - Age, Gender, Income, etc.
		○ Psychographic - Opinions and sentiments
		○ Geographic - Location
2) Data Understanding
	• Univariate distribution (Including target distribution) - Histogram
	• Bivariate with target - Scatter plots
3) Data Preparation
	• Numerical - Correlation plot
	• Categorical - Chi-square test of independence
	• Down sampling
	• Scaling
	• Redundant variable removal
	• PCA dimensionality reduction - Experimented and eliminated
4) Modeling
	• ML
		○ Logistic
		○ KNN
		○ Naïve Bayes
		○ Random Forest
		○ XGBoost
	• DL
5) Evaluation
	• Refining: Grid Search CV
	• Metrics: 
		○ Primary: Recall
		○ Secondary: Precision, accuracy, F1 score
	• Plots:
		○ ROC curve
6) Deployment
	• Power BI Dashboard - for companies to leverage suitable model

